00:33:51,809 --> 00:33:54,029
there's so many levels on which we can talk about this,

899
00:33:54,029 --> 00:33:56,609
but why was Rome victorious?

900
00:33:56,609 --> 00:33:58,498
- Well, the Punic Wars, really,

901
00:33:58,500 --> 00:34:00,750
almost always comes down to the Second Punic War.

902
00:34:00,750 --> 00:34:02,310
There's three. There's three Punic wars.

903
00:34:02,309 --> 00:34:03,899
The first is over Sicily. Rome wins.

904
00:34:03,900 --> 00:34:06,719
The second is the big one.

905
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:08,070
And it's the big one

906
00:34:08,070 --> 00:34:10,290
because Carthage, at this point in time,

907
00:34:10,289 --> 00:34:11,339
just by sheer luck,

908
00:34:11,340 --> 00:34:13,830
coughs up one of the greatest military geniuses

909
00:34:13,829 --> 00:34:15,898
in all of history.

910
00:34:15,900 --> 00:34:18,330
This guy, Hannibal Barca.

911
00:34:18,329 --> 00:34:21,569
He was actually the son of the Carthaginian general

912
00:34:21,570 --> 00:34:22,830
who fought Rome for Sicily.

913
00:34:22,829 --> 00:34:23,968
Hamilcar was his father.

914
00:34:23,969 --> 00:34:26,998
But Hannibal is this just genius,

915
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:29,790
just absolute military genius.

916
00:34:29,789 --> 00:34:32,068
He goes to Spain,

917
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:34,889
he's the one who kind of organizes stuff there,

918
00:34:34,889 --> 00:34:38,668
and now he knows the second war with Rome is inevitable.

919
00:34:38,670 --> 00:34:41,190
And so the question is, how do you take down Rome?

920
00:34:41,190 --> 00:34:42,023
He's smart.

921
00:34:42,023 --> 00:34:43,260
He's seen Rome strength.

922
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:45,690
He knows it's the Italian allies.

923
00:34:45,690 --> 00:34:47,280
So Rome always wins,

924
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:48,959
because even if they lose battles,

925
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:51,180
they go to the Italian allies and half citizens

926
00:34:51,179 --> 00:34:52,649
and raise new armies.

927
00:34:52,650 --> 00:34:54,180
So how do you beat them?

928
00:34:54,179 --> 00:34:57,089
He can never raise that many troops himself.

929
00:34:57,090 --> 00:35:00,509
And Hannibal, I think, correctly figures out

930
00:35:00,510 --> 00:35:02,699
the one way to maybe defeat Rome

931
00:35:02,699 --> 00:35:04,708
is to cut them away from their allies.

932
00:35:04,710 --> 00:35:06,270
Well, how do you do this?

933
00:35:06,269 --> 00:35:07,438
Hannibal's plan is,

934
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:09,509
I'm not gonna wait and fight the Romans

935
00:35:09,510 --> 00:35:11,370
in Spain or North Africa.

936
00:35:11,369 --> 00:35:13,708
I'm gonna invade Italy.

937
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:15,420
So I'm gonna strike at the heart

938
00:35:15,420 --> 00:35:18,480
of this growing Roman Empire.

939
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:21,180
And my hope is that if I can win

940
00:35:21,179 --> 00:35:24,449
a couple big battles against Rome in Italy,

941
00:35:24,449 --> 00:35:27,449
the Italians will want their freedom back,

942
00:35:27,449 --> 00:35:29,039
and they'll rebel from Rome

943
00:35:29,039 --> 00:35:30,958
and maybe even join me.

944
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:32,730
Because most people who have been conquered

945
00:35:32,730 --> 00:35:33,840
want their freedom back,

946
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:36,989
so this is a reasonable plan.

947
00:35:36,989 --> 00:35:40,348
So Hannibal famously crosses the Alps with elephants.

948
00:35:40,349 --> 00:35:41,339
Dramatic stuff.

949
00:35:41,340 --> 00:35:42,690
Nobody expects him to do this.

950
00:35:42,690 --> 00:35:44,490
Nobody thinks you can do this.

951
00:35:44,489 --> 00:35:46,138
Shows up in northern Italy,

952
00:35:46,139 --> 00:35:47,399
Romans send an army,

953
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:48,720
Hannibal massacres them.

954
00:35:48,719 --> 00:35:50,489
He is a military genius.

955
00:35:50,489 --> 00:35:51,989
Rome takes a year,

956
00:35:51,989 --> 00:35:54,388
raises a second army, we know this story,

957
00:35:54,389 --> 00:35:55,588
sends it against Hannibal,

958
00:35:55,590 --> 00:35:56,793
Hannibal wipes 'em out.

959
00:35:57,630 --> 00:35:59,136
Rome gets clever this time.

960
00:35:59,135 --> 00:36:00,749
They say, "Okay, Hannibal's different.

961
00:36:00,750 --> 00:36:02,610
We're gonna take two years,

962
00:36:02,610 --> 00:36:03,930
raise two armies,

963
00:36:03,929 --> 00:36:07,379
and send them both out at the same time against Hannibal."

964
00:36:07,380 --> 00:36:08,329
So they do this,

