00:36:08,329 --> 00:36:09,720
and this is the Battle of Cannae,

966
00:36:09,719 --> 00:36:13,109
which is one of the most famous battles in history.

967
00:36:13,110 --> 00:36:17,459
Hannibal is facing this army of 80,000 Romans about,

968
00:36:17,460 --> 00:36:20,310
and he comes up with a strategy called Double Envelopment.

969
00:36:20,309 --> 00:36:21,779
I mean, we can go into it later if you want,

970
00:36:21,780 --> 00:36:22,949
but it's this famous strategy

971
00:36:22,949 --> 00:36:25,078
where he basically kind of sucks the Romans in,

972
00:36:25,079 --> 00:36:27,029
surrounds them on all sides,

973
00:36:27,030 --> 00:36:30,389
and in one afternoon, at the Battle of Cannae,

974
00:36:30,389 --> 00:36:35,389
Hannibal kills about 60,000 Romans.

975
00:36:36,210 --> 00:36:38,549
Now, just to put that in perspective,

976
00:36:38,550 --> 00:36:41,340
that's more Romans hacked to death

