00:37:44,849 --> 00:37:47,009
So what do they do about Hannibal?

1004
00:37:47,010 --> 00:37:48,750
Well, they're smart.

1005
00:37:48,750 --> 00:37:50,070
We're not gonna fight him.

1006
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:51,540
We're not gonna give Hannibal

1007
00:37:51,539 --> 00:37:53,579
the chance to kill more Romans.

1008
00:37:53,579 --> 00:37:57,148
So they adopt a strategy that they'll follow Hannibal,

1009
00:37:57,150 --> 00:37:58,500
or they raise a couple more armies,

1010
00:37:58,500 --> 00:38:00,179
follow Hannibal around,

1011
00:38:00,179 --> 00:38:02,549
but whenever Hannibal turns and tries to attack them,

1012
00:38:02,550 --> 00:38:03,816
the Romans just back off.

1013
00:38:03,817 --> 00:38:04,919
"No, thank you.

1014
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:07,199
We're not gonna let you, give you a chance."

1015
00:38:07,199 --> 00:38:08,032
Meanwhile, though,

1016
00:38:08,032 --> 00:38:10,379
they're not scared of other Carthaginians.

1017
00:38:10,380 --> 00:38:12,090
So they raise a couple more armies

1018
00:38:12,090 --> 00:38:14,520
and they send these to Spain, for example,

1019
00:38:14,519 --> 00:38:17,938
and start attacking the Carthaginian holdings there.

1020
00:38:17,940 --> 00:38:20,190
And by luck or necessity,

1021
00:38:20,190 --> 00:38:22,230
Rome comes up with its own brilliant commander

1022
00:38:22,230 --> 00:38:24,629
at this point, a guy named Scipio.

1023
00:38:24,630 --> 00:38:27,839
And he wins victories in Spain, conquer Spain.

1024
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:30,029
Then he crosses into North Africa

1025
00:38:30,030 --> 00:38:31,469
and starts to conquer that

1026
00:38:31,469 --> 00:38:34,319
and ends up threatening Carthage directly.

1027
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:38,040
And poor Hannibal, undefeated in Italy,

1028
00:38:38,039 --> 00:38:40,079
has now been walking up and down Italy,

1029
00:38:40,079 --> 00:38:43,769
or marching up and down Italy for 12 years,

1030
00:38:43,769 --> 00:38:45,509
looking for another fight.

