00:39:06,630 --> 00:39:08,400
are kind of old by this point.

1042
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,079
Scipio has all the advantages.

1043
00:39:10,079 --> 00:39:11,851
He wins. Carthage is defeated.

1044
00:39:12,719 --> 00:39:15,118
So that's pretty much the end of Carthage.

1045
00:39:15,119 --> 00:39:16,288
The city survives,

1046
00:39:16,289 --> 00:39:17,279
and then 50 years later,

1047
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:18,419
the Romans wipe it out,

1048
00:39:18,420 --> 00:39:20,400
but that's not much of a war.

1049
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:22,200
But from this moment on,

1050
00:39:22,199 --> 00:39:25,859
from the Second Punic War, which ends in 201 BC,

1051
00:39:25,860 --> 00:39:29,970
Rome is, undisputably, the most powerful force,

1052
00:39:29,969 --> 00:39:32,368
nation in the Mediterranean world.

1053
00:39:32,369 --> 00:39:34,048
And having conquered the west,

1054
00:39:34,050 --> 00:39:35,820
they're now gonna turn to the east,

1055
00:39:35,820 --> 00:39:37,739
which is the Greek world.

1056
00:39:37,739 --> 00:39:39,779
And the Greek world is older,

1057
00:39:39,780 --> 00:39:40,979
it's richer,

1058
00:39:40,980 --> 00:39:43,319
it's the rich part half of the Mediterranean,

1059
00:39:43,320 --> 00:39:45,659
it's culturally more sophisticated.

1060
00:39:45,659 --> 00:39:47,699
It's the world left by Alexander the Great,

1061
