00:44:53,340 --> 00:44:55,770
where you kind of make the shields overlap

1200
00:44:55,769 --> 00:44:58,259
and just form this solid mass

1201
00:44:58,260 --> 00:44:59,790
bristling with spear points

1202
00:44:59,789 --> 00:45:02,099
and just slowly kind of march forward

1203
00:45:02,099 --> 00:45:04,498
and grind up your enemy in front of you.

1204
00:45:04,500 --> 00:45:07,230
And so that sort of block of heavy infantry.

1205
00:45:07,230 --> 00:45:08,399
The advantage is,

1206
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:09,870
head on, against other things,

1207
00:45:09,869 --> 00:45:11,008
they tend to win.

1208
00:45:11,010 --> 00:45:13,442
The disadvantage is, it's slow moving,

1209
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:16,679
it's vulnerable from the sides and the rear,

1210
00:45:16,679 --> 00:45:18,419
so you gotta protect those.

1211
00:45:18,420 --> 00:45:20,549
But if you can keep frontally faced,

1212
00:45:20,550 --> 00:45:22,980
it's pretty much invincible.

1213
00:45:22,980 --> 00:45:26,670
And that's taken even further by Alexander the Great

1214
00:45:26,670 --> 00:45:28,589
who comes up with the idea,

1215
00:45:28,590 --> 00:45:30,900
well, what if we even give them a longer spear?

