03:12:39,059 --> 03:12:41,999
Attila goes back and says, "Eh, I changed my mind.

5198
03:12:42,000 --> 03:12:43,470
We're gonna go back up to France,

5199
03:12:43,469 --> 03:12:44,459
hang around for another year,

5200
03:12:44,459 --> 03:12:46,499
we'll finish off the Romans later."

5201
03:12:46,500 --> 03:12:49,020
And, you know, Christian sources say,

5202
03:12:49,020 --> 03:12:51,831
saints appeared in the sky with flaming swords

5203
03:12:51,832 --> 03:12:54,239
and, you know, scared away Attila.

5204
03:12:54,239 --> 03:12:55,468
Some other sources say,

5205
03:12:55,469 --> 03:12:57,509
well, the Pope gave Attila a huge bribe

5206
03:12:57,510 --> 03:12:59,189
to go away for a while.

5207
03:12:59,190 --> 03:13:01,529
Believe whichever you like.

5208
03:13:01,530 --> 03:13:04,559
But then Attila ends up dying on his wedding night

5209
03:13:04,559 --> 03:13:08,009
before he comes back under mysterious circumstances,

5210
03:13:08,010 --> 03:13:09,960
and so that never materializes

5211
03:13:09,959 --> 03:13:12,479
and the Huns kind of fragment after his death.

5212
03:13:12,479 --> 03:13:16,738
- So what was the definitive blow by the barbarians,

5213
03:13:16,739 --> 03:13:17,908
by the Visigoths?

5214
03:13:17,909 --> 03:13:20,699
- The barbarians are so many different groups,

5215
03:13:20,700 --> 03:13:23,130
and weirdly, I think an important one

5216
03:13:23,129 --> 03:13:24,508
that sometimes people tend to focus

5217
03:13:24,510 --> 03:13:26,370
on the Huns and the Goths.

5218
03:13:26,370 --> 03:13:29,999
The Vandals end up going to Spain,

5219
03:13:30,000 --> 03:13:31,260
conquering Spain,

5220
03:13:31,260 --> 03:13:33,506
and then crossing over into North Africa

5221
03:13:33,506 --> 03:13:36,239
and kind of conquering North Africa as well.

5222
03:13:36,239 --> 03:13:38,039
And Spain and North Africa

5223
03:13:38,040 --> 03:13:41,520
were some of the main areas

5224
03:13:41,520 --> 03:13:44,250
that food surpluses were collected from

5225
03:13:44,250 --> 03:13:46,950
and sent to Rome to feed the city of Rome.

5226
03:13:46,950 --> 03:13:49,680
And it's after those Vandal invasions

5227
03:13:49,680 --> 03:13:51,119
or the takeover of those areas

5228
03:13:51,120 --> 03:13:53,789
that the population of Rome plummets.

5229
03:13:53,790 --> 03:13:55,770
So I think that's an interesting moment

5230
03:13:55,770 --> 03:13:57,209
where, you know, the city of Rome

5231
03:13:57,209 --> 03:13:58,769
had always been this symbol

5232
03:13:58,770 --> 03:14:01,319
and already it was no longer the capital.

5233
03:14:01,319 --> 03:14:03,269
The emperors had moved to Ravenna,

5234
03:14:03,270 --> 03:14:04,499
a little bit north,

5235
03:14:04,500 --> 03:14:06,360
because it was surrounded by swamps,

5236
03:14:06,360 --> 03:14:07,920
so it was more defensible.

5237
03:14:07,920 --> 03:14:09,059
But there is something important

5238
03:14:09,059 --> 03:14:10,978
about that old symbolic capital

5239
03:14:10,979 --> 03:14:12,358
now just collapsing

5240
03:14:12,360 --> 03:14:14,670
in terms of population numbers

5241
03:14:14,670 --> 03:14:16,380
really no longer having importance

5242
03:14:16,379 --> 03:14:20,069
because, literally, its food supply is cut off

5243
03:14:20,069 --> 03:14:22,859
by losing those areas of the empire.

5244
03:14:22,860 --> 03:14:24,303
And of course the capital,

5245
03:14:25,290 --> 03:14:28,589
Constantine had founded a new second capital

5246
03:14:28,590 --> 03:14:30,239
at what used to be Byzantium,

5247
03:14:30,239 --> 03:14:31,648
a Greek city on the Bosporus,

5248
03:14:31,649 --> 03:14:33,568
which becomes Constantinople.

5249
03:14:33,569 --> 03:14:36,569
He names it not very modestly after himself.

5250
03:14:36,569 --> 03:14:39,089
And that now is really the dominant city

5251
03:14:39,090 --> 03:14:41,040
for any of the Roman empires,

5252
03:14:41,040 --> 03:14:42,150
Eastern or Western.

5253
03:14:42,149 --> 03:14:43,492
- So if you're actually living in that century,

5254
03:14:43,493 --> 03:14:45,240
the 5th century,

5255
03:14:45,239 --> 03:14:47,609
it's kind of like the Western Roman Empire dies

5256
03:14:47,610 --> 03:14:48,900
with a whimper.

5257
03:14:48,899 --> 03:14:50,462
It's not like,

5258
03:14:50,462 --> 03:14:52,379
it's a bunch of strikes. - Yeah.

5259
03:14:52,379 --> 03:14:53,249
- There's a lot of moments you can pick.

5260
03:14:53,250 --> 03:14:54,960
There's an earlier one in the 300s

5261
03:14:54,959 --> 03:14:56,009
when the Roman Empire,

5262
03:14:56,010 --> 03:14:58,230
the Romans lose a big battle

5263
03:14:58,229 --> 03:15:00,029
to, you know, some barbarians

5264
03:15:00,030 --> 03:15:01,740
that, symbolically, is important.

5265
03:15:01,739 --> 03:15:04,469
But yeah, I don't think there's one clear cut moment.

5266
03:15:04,469 --> 03:15:06,538
And again, I don't know that it is the barbarians

5267
03:15:06,540 --> 03:15:07,537
that cause, quote,

5268
03:15:07,537 --> 03:15:09,311
"the fall of the Roman Empire."

5269
03:15:09,310 --> 03:15:10,289
I mean, this is the other game,

5270
03:15:10,290 --> 03:15:11,190
as people like to say,

5271
03:15:11,190 --> 03:15:13,319
when did the Roman Empire fall?

5272
03:15:13,319 --> 03:15:15,988
The other big question is why,

5273
03:15:15,989 --> 03:15:18,629
you know, why did the Roman Empire fall?

5274
03:15:18,629 --> 03:15:20,849
If you define it as falling.

5275
03:15:20,850 --> 03:15:24,479
And I mean barbarian invasions was the traditional answer.

5276
03:15:24,479 --> 03:15:26,342
So there's a French historian famously said,

5277
03:15:26,343 --> 03:15:28,560
"The Roman Empire didn't fall,

5278
03:15:28,559 --> 03:15:29,549
it was murdered.

5279
03:15:29,549 --> 03:15:32,308
You know, it was killed by barbarians."

5280
03:15:32,309 --> 03:15:34,622
But I mean, there's other explanations.

5281
03:15:35,850 --> 03:15:37,380
You know, I mean, some people say

5282
03:15:37,379 --> 03:15:38,578
it was Christianity,

5283
03:15:38,579 --> 03:15:41,639
some say it was a climate.

5284
03:15:41,639 --> 03:15:46,379
That the Roman Empire flourished during this moment of luck

5285
03:15:46,379 --> 03:15:47,909
when just the climate was good,

5286
03:15:47,909 --> 03:15:50,759
and then you get this sort of late Roman little ice age,

5287
03:15:50,760 --> 03:15:52,260
and everything goes downhill,

5288
03:15:52,260 --> 03:15:53,823
and that's what caused it.

5289
03:15:54,780 --> 03:15:56,640
There's some that say things like disease.

5290
03:15:56,639 --> 03:16:00,208
There were a whole series of waves of plague

5291
03:16:00,209 --> 03:16:02,548
that started to hit under Marcus Aurelius

5292
03:16:02,549 --> 03:16:04,169
and continued after him,

5293
03:16:04,170 --> 03:16:07,560
which seemed to caused real serious death

5294
03:16:07,559 --> 03:16:09,359
and economic disruption.

5295
03:16:09,360 --> 03:16:11,520
I mean, that's a decent explanation.

5296
03:16:11,520 --> 03:16:13,830
Another popular one is moral decline,

5297
03:16:13,829 --> 03:16:16,029
which I don't think really works well.

5298
03:16:16,030 --> 03:16:18,179
You even get the people saying, you know, lead poisoning,

5299
03:16:18,180 --> 03:16:19,680
but that's not true,

5300
03:16:19,680 --> 03:16:21,240
'cause they were drinking outta the same pipes

5301
03:16:21,239 --> 03:16:23,219
when the empire was expanding, right?

5302
03:16:23,219 --> 03:16:24,479
- Yeah, that's fascinating.

5303
03:16:24,479 --> 03:16:25,312
That's fascinating.

5304
03:16:25,313 --> 03:16:27,729
But often, we kind of agree

5305
03:16:28,799 --> 03:16:31,529
that's something that you've talked about quite a bit

5306
03:16:31,530 --> 03:16:32,840
is the military perspective

5307
03:16:32,840 --> 03:16:34,509
is the one that defines

5308
03:16:35,489 --> 03:16:38,038
the rise and fall of empires.

5309
03:16:38,040 --> 03:16:40,056
You have a really great lecture series called

5310
03:16:40,057 --> 03:16:43,830
"The Decisive Battles of World History,"

5311
03:16:43,829 --> 03:16:45,629
which is another fascinating perspective

5312
03:16:45,629 --> 03:16:47,579
to look at world's history.

5313
03:16:47,579 --> 03:16:50,219
What makes a battle decisive?

5314
03:16:50,219 --> 03:16:51,269
- The easiest definition

5315
03:16:51,270 --> 03:16:54,299
is it causes an immediate change

5316
03:16:54,299 --> 03:16:56,279
in political structure.

5317
03:16:56,280 --> 03:16:57,750
So who's in charge?

5318
03:16:57,750 --> 03:17:00,450
So the classic decisive political battle

5319
03:17:00,450 --> 03:17:03,659
is Alexander beats King Darius III

5320
03:17:03,659 --> 03:17:05,189
at the Battle of Gaugamela.

5321
03:17:05,190 --> 03:17:06,510
And in that moment,

5322
03:17:06,510 --> 03:17:10,710
we switch from the ruler of the entire huge Persian Empire

5323
03:17:10,709 --> 03:17:11,819
being Darius

5324
03:17:11,819 --> 03:17:13,349
to now being Alexander.

5325
03:17:13,350 --> 03:17:14,519
From it being Persian

5326
03:17:14,520 --> 03:17:16,380
to being controlled by the Macedonians.

5327
03:17:16,379 --> 03:17:18,298
So there is a one afternoon

5328
03:17:18,299 --> 03:17:20,279
has this dramatic switch over

5329
03:17:20,280 --> 03:17:22,949
a enormous geographic area, right?

5330
03:17:22,950 --> 03:17:24,570
So that's a decisive battle

5331
03:17:24,569 --> 03:17:27,089
in that you see that immediate change.

5332
03:17:27,090 --> 03:17:28,860
Other types of decisive battles

5333
03:17:28,860 --> 03:17:32,279
are ones that might have more unforeseen long-term effects.

5334
03:17:32,280 --> 03:17:34,889
You know, you may not realize this is decisive at the time,

5335
03:17:34,889 --> 03:17:37,529
but from a longer perspective, it is.

5336
03:17:37,530 --> 03:17:40,829
And often those are ones that either

5337
03:17:40,829 --> 03:17:43,529
allow some new people

5338
03:17:43,530 --> 03:17:46,679
or idea or institution

5339
03:17:46,680 --> 03:17:50,249
to either grow or have its growth curbed.

5340
03:17:50,250 --> 03:17:51,570
So at various points,

5341
03:17:51,569 --> 03:17:53,519
we have, you know, empires that were expanding

5342
03:17:53,520 --> 03:17:56,040
and basically were stopped at some battle.

5343
03:17:56,040 --> 03:17:57,719
And so you say, well, if they hadn't been stopped there,

5344
03:17:57,719 --> 03:18:00,268
they might have gone on to dominate this whole area.

5345
03:18:00,270 --> 03:18:05,100
Or conversely, you know, you could say Rome wasn't,

5346
03:18:05,100 --> 03:18:07,950
they were one place before the Second Punic War,

5347
03:18:07,950 --> 03:18:10,829
after the Second Punic War, they were this dominant force.

5348
03:18:10,829 --> 03:18:11,812
So you could pick one of those battles

5349
03:18:11,813 --> 03:18:13,319
and say that was decisive

5350
03:18:13,319 --> 03:18:15,749
in setting them on this new path.

5351
03:18:15,750 --> 03:18:18,629
- It's also an opportunity to demonstrate a new technology,

5352
03:18:18,629 --> 03:18:20,609
and if that technology is effective-

5353
03:18:20,610 --> 03:18:22,230
- Yes. - it changes history

5354
03:18:22,229 --> 03:18:26,639
because that was done as either tactical

5355
03:18:26,639 --> 03:18:29,909
or literally the technology used.

5356
03:18:29,909 --> 03:18:32,339
So how important is technology,

5357
03:18:32,340 --> 03:18:34,650
the technological advantage in war?

5358
03:18:34,649 --> 03:18:37,408
- Huge. I mean, the history of warfare

5359
03:18:37,409 --> 03:18:41,099
is basically the history of technological change often.

5360
03:18:41,100 --> 03:18:43,769
So, I mean, there's all the great moments of transition.

5361
03:18:43,770 --> 03:18:45,419
For a long time, we fought with,

5362
03:18:45,420 --> 03:18:47,250
you know, hand to hand,

5363
03:18:47,250 --> 03:18:48,782
with metal weapons,

5364
03:18:49,709 --> 03:18:52,168
then you start to have the gunpowder revolution,

5365
03:18:52,170 --> 03:18:54,870
which causes all sorts of shifts there.

5366
03:18:54,870 --> 03:18:56,999
You know, there's big changes.

5367
03:18:57,000 --> 03:18:58,860
Planes, when they become a huge force.

5368
03:18:58,860 --> 03:19:01,619
I mean, World War II is this crazy time

5369
03:19:01,620 --> 03:19:04,110
where planes go from literally biplanes,

5370
03:19:04,110 --> 03:19:06,869
you know, string and wood, to jets,

5371
03:19:06,870 --> 03:19:08,013
four years later.

5372
03:19:09,239 --> 03:19:10,468
So that's this moment

5373
03:19:10,469 --> 03:19:12,808
of incredibly fast technological change.

5374
03:19:12,809 --> 03:19:13,889
You know, going into World War II,

5375
03:19:13,889 --> 03:19:15,599
everybody thinks it's all about battleships,

5376
03:19:15,600 --> 03:19:17,340
who's got the biggest battleships.

5377
03:19:17,340 --> 03:19:18,240
Four years later,

5378
03:19:18,239 --> 03:19:19,707
battleships are just junk.

5379
03:19:19,708 --> 03:19:21,450
Let's just scrap 'em.

5380
03:19:21,450 --> 03:19:23,070
It's all about aircraft and carriers.

5381
03:19:23,069 --> 03:19:25,859
And that's everything war at sea.

5382
03:19:25,860 --> 03:19:27,390
So you have these moments of,

5383
03:19:27,389 --> 03:19:28,409
particularly in warfare,

5384
03:19:28,409 --> 03:19:30,598
almost accelerated technological change

5385
03:19:30,600 --> 03:19:33,780
where things happen very rapidly

5386
03:19:33,780 --> 03:19:36,210
and the civilization

5387
03:19:36,209 --> 03:19:37,829
or the nation or the army

5388
03:19:37,829 --> 03:19:41,159
that adapts more quickly to the new technology

5389
03:19:41,159 --> 03:19:42,808
will often be the one that wins.

5390
03:19:42,809 --> 03:19:44,279
And we've seen that story

5391
03:19:44,280 --> 03:19:46,562
over and over and over again in history.

5392
03:19:47,700 --> 03:19:49,619
- It's also interesting how much geography

5393
03:19:49,620 --> 03:19:51,509
that you mentioned a few times

5394
03:19:51,510 --> 03:19:54,329
affects wars.

5395
03:19:54,329 --> 03:19:55,498
The result of wars,

5396
03:19:55,500 --> 03:19:57,959
the rise and fall of empires,

5397
03:19:57,959 --> 03:20:00,119
all of it, as silly as it is,

5398
03:20:00,120 --> 03:20:01,590
it's not the people or the technology,

5399
03:20:01,590 --> 03:20:02,819
it's like, sometimes, like literally,

5400
03:20:02,819 --> 03:20:04,258
that there's rivers.

5401
03:20:04,260 --> 03:20:07,340
- I think there's a real geographic determinism

5402
03:20:07,340 --> 03:20:09,300
to civilization itself.

5403
03:20:09,299 --> 03:20:12,299
I mean, you know, if you look at where civilization arose,

5404
03:20:12,299 --> 03:20:13,619
it's in Mesopotamia

5405
03:20:13,620 --> 03:20:16,050
in sort of a swampy land between two rivers.

5406
03:20:16,049 --> 03:20:18,178
It's in the Nile River Delta,

5407
03:20:18,180 --> 03:20:20,189
where it's the same situation.

5408
03:20:20,190 --> 03:20:21,450
It's in the Indus River

5409
03:20:21,450 --> 03:20:22,500
where you have the same thing.

5410
03:20:22,500 --> 03:20:23,909
And it's along the Yellow Rivers

5411
03:20:23,909 --> 03:20:24,959
and the Yangtze Rivers

5412
03:20:24,959 --> 03:20:26,309
where it's the same thing.

5413
03:20:26,309 --> 03:20:29,128
So I mean, that is geographically determined

5414
03:20:29,129 --> 03:20:31,439
where those great civilizations

5415
03:20:31,440 --> 03:20:33,273
of, you know, Asia,

5416
03:20:34,139 --> 03:20:36,208
you know, or Europe are gonna arise

5417
03:20:36,209 --> 03:20:38,758
is it's very much determined by that.

5418
03:20:38,760 --> 03:20:41,359
And often, the course of history

5419
03:20:41,359 --> 03:20:44,730
has that strong geographical determination.

5420
03:20:44,729 --> 03:20:47,128
I mean, you can argue that all of Egyptian,

5421
03:20:47,129 --> 03:20:49,769
Ancient Egyptian society,

5422
03:20:49,770 --> 03:20:54,480
is kind of based around the cycle of the Nile flood

5423
03:20:54,479 --> 03:20:56,368
because it was so predictable,

5424
03:20:56,370 --> 03:20:57,930
and everything depended on it,

5425
03:20:57,930 --> 03:21:00,596
and their whole religion actually develops around that.

5426
03:21:00,596 --> 03:21:02,789
And in Mesopotamia, the same thing.

5427
03:21:02,790 --> 03:21:04,320
The way their religion develops

5428
03:21:04,319 --> 03:21:08,429
is a reaction to the particular geographic environment

5429
03:21:08,430 --> 03:21:10,709
that those people grew up in.

5430
03:21:10,709 --> 03:21:15,058
So that's a very profound influence on civilization.

5431
03:21:15,059 --> 03:21:17,099
One of my professors once said to me,

5432
03:21:17,100 --> 03:21:20,220
the best map of the Roman Empire

5433
03:21:20,219 --> 03:21:22,739
isn't any of these maps with political borders.

5434
03:21:22,739 --> 03:21:25,439
It would be a map that shows the zone

5435
03:21:25,440 --> 03:21:28,589
in which it's possible to cultivate olives.

5436
03:21:28,590 --> 03:21:30,420
So if you simply get a map

5437
03:21:30,420 --> 03:21:32,940
and map onto it where you could grow olives

5438
03:21:32,940 --> 03:21:33,960
during this time,

5439
03:21:33,959 --> 03:21:36,179
let's say 1st century AD,

5440
03:21:36,180 --> 03:21:38,550
it corresponds exactly,

5441
03:21:38,549 --> 03:21:40,558
I mean, really closely

5442
03:21:40,559 --> 03:21:43,889
to the areas that are most heavily Romanized.

5443
03:21:43,889 --> 03:21:47,098
Now, I'm not gonna say that, you know,

5444
03:21:47,100 --> 03:21:48,180
but there is something to that.

5445
03:21:48,180 --> 03:21:50,550
Where Roman culture spread successfully

5446
03:21:50,549 --> 03:21:53,461
is where people grow the same crops.

5447
03:21:54,329 --> 03:21:56,849
And that's just one of those fundamental things.

5448
03:21:56,850 --> 03:21:59,160
- Yeah, I mean, you so beautifully put

5449
03:21:59,159 --> 03:22:02,339
that the perspective can change dramatically

5450
03:22:02,340 --> 03:22:04,106
how you see history.

5451
03:22:04,105 --> 03:22:07,138
I mean, you could probably tell world history through what?

5452
03:22:07,139 --> 03:22:09,449
Through olives, cinnamon, and gold.

5453
03:22:09,450 --> 03:22:10,290
- Uh-huh.

5454
03:22:10,290 --> 03:22:11,580
Yeah. That's become really trendy

5455
03:22:11,579 --> 03:22:13,049
is to look at history through objects.

5456
03:22:13,049 --> 03:22:14,728
And I mean, for the Romans,

5457
03:22:14,729 --> 03:22:16,979
diet is huge.

5458
03:22:16,979 --> 03:22:17,812
I mean, you know,

5459
03:22:17,813 --> 03:22:20,220
probably 80% of of the people in their own world

5460
03:22:20,219 --> 03:22:23,611
ate basically a diet of olive oil, wine,

