5494
03:23:45,479 --> 03:23:47,158
which I teach in Wisconsin,

5495
03:23:47,159 --> 03:23:48,719
Green Bay, Wisconsin,

5496
03:23:48,719 --> 03:23:50,579
that Roman would step out, look around,

5497
03:23:50,579 --> 03:23:51,412
see all the beer,

5498
03:23:51,413 --> 03:23:52,980
the broths, and the cheese,

5499
03:23:52,979 --> 03:23:55,048
and say, "I know who you guys are.

5500
03:23:55,049 --> 03:23:56,669
- Yeah. - You're barbarians.

5501
03:23:56,670 --> 03:23:57,839
- Barbarians.

5502
03:23:57,840 --> 03:23:59,940
That's another way to draw the boundary

5503
03:23:59,940 --> 03:24:01,530
between olive oil, wine, and wheat

5504
03:24:01,530 --> 03:24:03,120
and meat, dairy, and beer.

5505
03:24:03,120 --> 03:24:04,230
- But it's more fundamental

5506
03:24:04,229 --> 03:24:06,298
because it's different forms of life.

5507
03:24:06,299 --> 03:24:08,339
- Yeah. - Because if you're a farmer,

5508
03:24:08,340 --> 03:24:09,600
you grow certain crops.

