03:29:52,829 --> 03:29:55,018
that are reflected in the modern world?

5659
03:29:55,020 --> 03:29:57,870
- Yeah, it's a book that my wife and I wrote together,

5660
03:29:57,870 --> 03:30:01,956
and it is trying to make people understand

5661
03:30:04,709 --> 03:30:08,548
how deeply rooted our current actions

5662
03:30:08,549 --> 03:30:09,599
in almost every way.

5663
03:30:09,600 --> 03:30:11,640
Even things that we think are just

5664
03:30:11,639 --> 03:30:15,449
in truly unique parts of our culture

5665
03:30:15,450 --> 03:30:18,209
or things that we think are just innate to human nature

5666
03:30:18,209 --> 03:30:19,858
are actually rooted in the past.

5667
03:30:19,860 --> 03:30:22,259
So this is another power of the past thing.

5668
03:30:22,260 --> 03:30:25,769
And this is just a long specific list of examples, really.

5669
03:30:25,770 --> 03:30:27,360
So, I mean, we go through government

5670
03:30:27,360 --> 03:30:29,759
and education and intellectual stuff

5671
03:30:29,760 --> 03:30:31,110
and art and architecture

5672
03:30:31,110 --> 03:30:32,364
and, you know, a lot of the things

5673
03:30:32,364 --> 03:30:34,289
that we've been talking about today.

5674
03:30:34,290 --> 03:30:37,530
Language, culture, medicine.

5675
03:30:37,530 --> 03:30:39,719
But even things like, you know, habits.

5676
03:30:39,719 --> 03:30:42,268
The way we celebrate things, the way we get married.

5677
03:30:42,270 --> 03:30:43,919
Our married rituals have all sorts of things

5678
03:30:43,920 --> 03:30:46,020
in common with Roman weddings.

